            },
            {
              "id": "eb-s1-body",
              "type": "text",
              "left": 24,
              "top": 120,
              "width": 950,
              "height": 300,
              "rotate": 0,
              "content": "<p style='font-size:18px;color:#cbd5e1;line-height:1.8;'><b style='color:#10b981;'>Imagine</b> you and all your friends have the exact same notebook. Every time someone writes something new, <b style='color:#f1f5f9;'>everyone's notebook automatically gets the same update</b>. And nobody \u2014 not even a teacher \u2014 can erase what's already written!</p><br/><p style='font-size:18px;color:#cbd5e1;line-height:1.8;'>That is a blockchain. Thousands of computers around the world all share the same digital notebook at once.</p>",
              "defaultFontName": "Inter",
              "defaultColor": "#cbd5e1"
            },
            {
